hubNumberofStackedChassis.name: hubNumberofStackedChassis
hubNumberofStackedChassis.description: Displays the total number of chassis in the stack.

hubStackReset.name: hubStackReset
hubStackReset.description: Resets all modules in all of the chassis in the stack.

hubLCDModeVariable.name: hubLCDModeVariable
hubLCDModeVariable.description: Sets the type of information displayed on the Management Module's LCD when in Sleep Mode. sysContact, sysLocation, and sysName are user-definable. Traps shows the most current SNMP trap message generated. Utilization shows the percentage of bandwidth used in each segment in the stack. Ipaddress shows the currently assigned Management Module IP address. Sleep text shows user-definable text set with the hubLCDSleepText object.

hubLCDSleepText.name: hubLCDSleepText
hubLCDSleepText.description: Sets user-defined text to be displayed by the LCD when in Sleep Mode. For example, you may want the name and phone number of a contact person to display on the LCD panel. This object is only applicable to 200 series stackable hubs.

hubLCDSleepTime.name: hubLCDSleepTime
hubLCDSleepTime.description: Sets the number of minutes before the LCD goes into Sleep Mode. If an LCD button isn't pressed for the time specified, the LCD goes into Sleep Mode and displays the information set by hubLCDModeVariable. To disable this feature, set the time to 0. This object is only applicable to 200 series stackable hubs.

hubRFC1516Segment.name: hubRFC1516Segment
hubRFC1516Segment.description: Sets which segment the standard repeater MIB (RFC1516) returns counters for. The standard repeater MIB doesn't support two segments at the same time.

chassisConfigTable.name: chassisConfigTable
chassisConfigTable.description: Configuration information at the chassis level.

chassisConfigEntry.name: chassisConfigEntry
chassisConfigEntry.description: A table entry, containing configuration information about a single chassis.

chassisConfigTableIndex.name: chassisConfigTableIndex
chassisConfigTableIndex.description: Chassis number in the stack. This object refers to the number in the example below. Example: chassisConfigTableIndex.1 This example refers to chassis 1 of the stack. The chassis at the top of the stack is number 1.

chassisSegmentMode.name: chassisSegmentMode
chassisSegmentMode.description: Sets/reports the repeater segment the chassis ports participate in. For chassis which do not support port speed autosensing, only 'segment1' or 'segment2' can be set. For stacks with both segments set to the same speed, setting a chassis to 'auto' causes linked ports to participate in segment2. The 'mixed' value is read-only and indicates that ports within the chassis do not share the same segment mode. Setting chassis ports via this object does not prevent ports from being set independently.

chassisReset.name: chassisReset
chassisReset.description: Resets all modules in the selected chassis.

chassisRPSState.name: chassisRPSState
chassisRPSState.description: The state of the optional Redundant Power Supply connected to the chassis. standby means the RPS is actively backing up the chassis. active means the chassis power supply has failed and the RPS is powering the chassis.

chassisIsolate.name: chassisIsolate
chassisIsolate.description: The isolated or unisolates the hub from the backplane channel.

moduleConfigStatusTable.name: moduleConfigStatusTable
moduleConfigStatusTable.description: Configuration and status information at the module level.

moduleConfigStatusEntry.name: moduleConfigStatusEntry
moduleConfigStatusEntry.description: A table entry, containing configuration and status information about a single module.

moduleChassisIndex.name: moduleChassisIndex
moduleChassisIndex.description: Chassis number in the stack. This object refers to the first number in the example below. Example: moduleChassisIndex.1.1 The first number is the chassis (hub) and the second number is the module in the chassis. This example refers to module 1 in hub 1 (which is the hub at the top of the stack). Base ports on the hub are always module 1. The left expansion slot (when facing the hub) is module 2 and the right expansion slot is module 3.

moduleIndex.name: moduleIndex
moduleIndex.description: Module number in the chassis. This object refers to the second number in the example below. Example: moduleChassisIndex.1.1 The first number is the chassis (hub) and the second number is the module in the chassis. This example refers to module 1 in hub 1 (which is the hub at the top of the stack). Base ports on the hub are always module 1. The left expansion slot (when facing the hub) is module 2 and the right expansion slot is module 3.

moduleType.name: moduleType
moduleType.description: The module type. The base ports of a 12- or 24-port hub are considered modules. For example, hubTXports12 are ports 1-12 on a 12-port hub. bridge is an externally inserted bridge and refers to the Ethernet Module or the Fiber Module. management is the Management Module (also called the SNMP agent). None means no module is installed.

moduleUserAssignedType.name: moduleUserAssignedType
moduleUserAssignedType.description: User-definable information about the type of the module. Manufacturer assigns a default value.

moduleUserAssignedNumber.name: moduleUserAssignedNumber
moduleUserAssignedNumber.description: User-definable information about the module. Blank by default.

moduleUserAssignedName.name: moduleUserAssignedName
moduleUserAssignedName.description: User-definable information about the module. Blank by default.

moduleHWDescription.name: moduleHWDescription
moduleHWDescription.description: Displays the CPU type and flash capacity.

moduleAgentSWVersion.name: moduleAgentSWVersion
moduleAgentSWVersion.description: Displays the module's agent software version. Each module has software which contributes to the SNMP agent's functionality. The Management Module version is the SNMP agent's version.

moduleBootSWVersion.name: moduleBootSWVersion
moduleBootSWVersion.description: Displays the module's boot software version.

moduleTotalPortCount.name: moduleTotalPortCount
moduleTotalPortCount.description: Displays the total number of ports in the module. This can be: 14 = a 12-port hub (12 base ports plus 2 expansion modules) 16 = a 12-port hub with an internal bridge (14, as described for a 12-port hub, plus 2 internal bridge ports) 24 = a 24-port hub 26 = a 24-port hub with an internal bridge 1 or 2 for an expansion module (module dependent).

moduleExternalPortCount.name: moduleExternalPortCount
moduleExternalPortCount.description: Number of external ports in the module.

moduleSegmentLockout.name: moduleSegmentLockout
moduleSegmentLockout.description: Prevents the hub speed from being changed by either a management station and/or the Change speed button on the front of a hub. Only nButtonnMgmt is valid for expansion modules. Only nButtonnMgmt or nButtonyMgmt is valid for hubs which do not have speed change buttons.

moduleMediaDevicesReset.name: moduleMediaDevicesReset
moduleMediaDevicesReset.description: Performs a physical layer reset of the module. Use this reset if ports lock-up on an individual hub.

moduleImageFileSource.name: moduleImageFileSource
moduleImageFileSource.description: Sets the IP address of the device that transfers the image file to the module. The image filename is specified by the moduleImageFileName object. The moduleImageDownloadControl object starts and stops the download process.

moduleImageFileName.name: moduleImageFileName
moduleImageFileName.description: Sets the image filename contained on the device specified by the moduleImageFileSource object. The moduleImageDownloadControl object starts and stops the download process to the module. e300agentImageUpdateCtrl must be set to enabled before starting the download process.

moduleImageDownloadControl.name: moduleImageDownloadControl
moduleImageDownloadControl.description: Starts and stops the image file download process to the module. Use the moduleImageFileSource to set the IP address of the device that contains image file. Use the moduleImageFileName object to set the image filename.

moduleImageDownloadStatus.name: moduleImageDownloadStatus
moduleImageDownloadStatus.description: Displays the Management Module's image file download status. If error appears, use the moduleImageFileSource, moduleImageFileName, and moduleImageDownloadControl objects to configure and download the image file to the module. Do not reset the module until the status has changed to completed.

moduleOperationalStatus.name: moduleOperationalStatus
moduleOperationalStatus.description: Current operational state of the module.

moduleUptime.name: moduleUptime
moduleUptime.description: Time since the module was last reset.

moduleSegmentMode.name: moduleSegmentMode
moduleSegmentMode.description: Sets/reports the repeater segment the module ports participate in. For modules which do not support automatic port speed selection, only 'segment1' or 'segment2' may be set. The 'mixed' value is read-only and indicates that ports within the module do not share the same segment mode. Setting module ports via this object does not prevent ports from being set independently.

moduleAllPortCounterReset.name: moduleAllPortCounterReset
moduleAllPortCounterReset.description: Resets all the port counters in the module to zero. This includes all traffic statistics (packet count, etc.) and error counts.

modulePersistentMemoryReset.name: modulePersistentMemoryReset
modulePersistentMemoryReset.description: Reset contents of persistent memory objects to factory defaults. Persistent memory object are settings that are saved even after the module is reset or power-cycled.

portConfigTable.name: portConfigTable
portConfigTable.description: Configuration information at the Port level.

portConfigEntry.name: portConfigEntry
portConfigEntry.description: A table entry, containing configuration information about a single port.

portChassisIndex.name: portChassisIndex
portChassisIndex.description: Chassis number in stack. This object refers to the first number in the example below. Example: portChassisIndex.1.1.9 The first number is the chassis. The second number is the module in the chassis. The third number is the port in the module. This example refers to port 9 in module 1 in hub 1 (which is the hub at the top of the stack). Base ports on the hub are always module 1. The left expansion slot (when facing the hub) is module 2 and the right expansion slot is module 3.

portModuleIndex.name: portModuleIndex
portModuleIndex.description: Module number in the chassis. This object refers to the second number in the example below. Example: portModuleIndex.1.1.9 The first number is the chassis. The second number is the module in the chassis. The third number is the port in the module. This example refers to port 9 in module 1 in hub 1 (which is the hub at the top of the stack). Base ports on the hub are always module 1. The left expansion slot (when facing the hub) is module 2 and the right expansion slot is module 3.

portIndex.name: portIndex
portIndex.description: Port number in the module. This object refers to the third number in the example below. Example: portChassisIndex 1.1.9 The first number is the chassis. The second number is the module in the chassis. The third number is the port in the module. This example refers to port 9 in module 1 in hub 1 (which is the hub at the top of the stack). Base ports on the hub are always module 1. The left expansion slot (when facing the hub) is module 2 and the right expansion slot is module 3.

portType.name: portType
portType.description: Displays the selected port's capabilities. internalHalfDuplex is the expansion module's internal connection to a port in the hub.

portAdminStatus.name: portAdminStatus
portAdminStatus.description: Enables or disables the selected port. Disabled ports will not be able to establish a link to a device. Disabled ports remain disabled until re-enabled.

portOperStatus.name: portOperStatus
portOperStatus.description: Displays the current link status of the port. Operational means a port has established a link to a device. Notoperational means the port does not have a link established. It does not mean there is a problem with the port. Notpresent may mean that an Intel Cascade Cable was removed from a hub or that the cable is faulty. Violated means that this port was disabled by a security violation. Port security is enabled/disabled with the portSecureAdminMode object. A violated port can be re-enabled with the portAdminStatus object.

portJabber.name: portJabber
portJabber.description: Jabber state of the port. Failure means the device attached to the port caused the hub's jabber lock-up protection to turn on. Check the device attached to the port.

portTimeSinceLastLinkChange.name: portTimeSinceLastLinkChange
portTimeSinceLastLinkChange.description: Time since the last link status change.

portAllCountersReset.name: portAllCountersReset
portAllCountersReset.description: Resets all counters for ports to zero. This includes all traffic statistics (packet count, etc.) and error counts.

portReset.name: portReset
portReset.description: Reset the port at the media level.

portLastErrorID.name: portLastErrorID
portLastErrorID.description: Type of last error that occurred on the port since the last link status change. badPhy is a hardware problem with the hub port. polarity means there's a cabling problem between the hub and the attached device. wrongSpeedLP means the device attached to the port is operating at the wrong speed. jabberSeen means you may have a faulty device attached to the port. partition means the port was automatically partitioned at least once.

portSegmentAdminMode.name: portSegmentAdminMode
portSegmentAdminMode.description: For ports that have the ability to be set independent of the hub or module they reside in, this object allows setting the port to 'segment1', 'segment2', or 'auto'.

portSegmentOperStatus.name: portSegmentOperStatus
portSegmentOperStatus.description: Reports the port's segment assignment. 'none' indicates the port has a portSegmentAdminMode of 'auto' and has not negotiated a link speed setting with a device.

portLinkSpeed.name: portLinkSpeed
portLinkSpeed.description: The operational speed of this port when linked. Ports which do not have a link report 'none'.

portSecureAdminMode.name: portSecureAdminMode
portSecureAdminMode.description: Causes a port to be administratively disabled if an un-authorized MAC address is detected as having transmitted a frame into this hub port. A trap is also generated when an unauthorized source MAC address is detected. An unauthorized source MAC addresss is defined as follows: If a portSecureMAC is specified, any frame received from this port which does not originate from the specified portSecureMAC is unauthorized. If no portSecureMAC is specified, the first source MAC address detected on this port is the authorized MAC. Any frame originating on this port with a different MAC address from the first MAC address detected is unauthorized. Older Management modules (those which do not support RMON) will not allow enabling of port security due to hardware limitations.

portSecureMAC.name: portSecureMAC
portSecureMAC.description: Specifies the authorized MAC address for this port if portSecureAdminMode is set to portSecurityOn.

portLinkTestState.name: portLinkTestState
portLinkTestState.description: The current setting of link test function for the port. When disable, a port will no longer be disconnected due to link fail. When enable, the port will only remain connected to the network so long as link pulses are being received.

portLinkTestStatusTrapCtrl.name: portLinkTestStatusTrapCtrl
portLinkTestStatusTrapCtrl.description: This object indicates whether a trap should be generated when the link state changes.

portSpeedStatusTrapCtrl.name: portSpeedStatusTrapCtrl
portSpeedStatusTrapCtrl.description: This object indicates whether a trap should be generated when the speed status changes.

portPolarityStatus.name: portPolarityStatus
portPolarityStatus.description: The current polarity status of this port.

rptrSegmentConfigTable.name: rptrSegmentConfigTable
rptrSegmentConfigTable.description: Repeater configuration information at the segment level.

rptrSegmentConfigEntry.name: rptrSegmentConfigEntry
rptrSegmentConfigEntry.description: A table entry, containing repeater configuration information about a single segment.

rptrSegmentConfigIndex.name: rptrSegmentConfigIndex
rptrSegmentConfigIndex.description: Index into this table is rptrSegmentConfigIndex. Any configuration changes apply to all repeater ports participating in the segment. If a stack does not have any ports at the selected speed, the OperationalStatus of this segment will be NotPresent.

rptrSegmentOperationalStatus.name: rptrSegmentOperationalStatus
rptrSegmentOperationalStatus.description: Displays the operational status of the segment.

rptrSegmentZeroCounters.name: rptrSegmentZeroCounters
rptrSegmentZeroCounters.description: Resets all repeater per-port counters of the repeater modules in the segment. The read value is always notreset.

rptrSegmentReset.name: rptrSegmentReset
rptrSegmentReset.description: Performs a cold-reset of all repeater modules in the segment. (RFC2108 rptrInfoReset)

rptrSegmentResetMedia.name: rptrSegmentResetMedia
rptrSegmentResetMedia.description: Performs a media layer reset of all repeater modules in the segment.

rptrSegmentPartitionThreshold.name: rptrSegmentPartitionThreshold
rptrSegmentPartitionThreshold.description: The number of consecutive collisions that will cause a port to autopartition. Note that this sets the value for all repeaters in the segment.

rptrSegmentNonDisruptTest.name: rptrSegmentNonDisruptTest
rptrSegmentNonDisruptTest.description: Performs a self-test of all repeater modules in the segment.

rptrSegmentUtilizationTrapThreshold.name: rptrSegmentUtilizationTrapThreshold
rptrSegmentUtilizationTrapThreshold.description: If the utilization rate exceeds this value, a trap is sent. Use 0 to disable. This trap is based on the utilization rate over the last rptrSegmentUtilizationTrapPeriod.

rptrSegmentCollisionTrapThreshold.name: rptrSegmentCollisionTrapThreshold
rptrSegmentCollisionTrapThreshold.description: If the number of collisions exceeds this value, a trap is sent. Use 0 to disable. This trap is based on the number of collision in the last rptrSegmentCollisionTrapPeriod.

rptrSegmentUtilizationTrapPeriod.name: rptrSegmentUtilizationTrapPeriod
rptrSegmentUtilizationTrapPeriod.description: Time period (in minutes) that segment utilization must exceed the trap threshold value to generate a trap.

rptrSegmentCollisionTrapPeriod.name: rptrSegmentCollisionTrapPeriod
rptrSegmentCollisionTrapPeriod.description: Time period (in minutes) that segment collisions must exceed the trap threshold value to generate a trap.

rptrSegmentSpeed.name: rptrSegmentSpeed
rptrSegmentSpeed.description: The speed of the ports within the segment.

rptrSegmentStatTable.name: rptrSegmentStatTable
rptrSegmentStatTable.description: Repeater status information at the segment level.

rptrSegmentStatEntry.name: rptrSegmentStatEntry
rptrSegmentStatEntry.description: A table entry, containing repeater status information about a single repeater.

rptrSegmentTotalFrames.name: rptrSegmentTotalFrames
rptrSegmentTotalFrames.description: The number of frames detected without errors. Includes unicast, broadcast, and multicast frames. Does not include frames received with frames too long, runt, FCS, or alignment errors. (RFC2108 rptrMonitorGroupTotalFrames for all groups in this segment.)

rptrSegmentTotalOctets.name: rptrSegmentTotalOctets
rptrSegmentTotalOctets.description: The number of octets (bytes) contained in frames received that had no errors. This includes octets in unicast, broadcast, and multicast frames. It also includes octets after the start frame delimiter up to FCS but not including FCS octets. (RFC2108 rptrMonitorGroupTotalOctets for all groups in this segment.)

rptrSegmentTotalErrors.name: rptrSegmentTotalErrors
rptrSegmentTotalErrors.description: The total number of errors detected. Total errors include FCS errors, alignment errors, frame too long, short events, late events, very long event, and rate mismatch errors. (RFC2108 rptrMonitorGroupTotalErrors for all groups in this segment.)

rptrSegmentTotalCollisions.name: rptrSegmentTotalCollisions
rptrSegmentTotalCollisions.description: Sum of all collisions in this segment. (RFC2108 rptrMonTxCollisions)

rptrSegmentPartitionedPorts.name: rptrSegmentPartitionedPorts
rptrSegmentPartitionedPorts.description: Total number of present and enabled, but autopartitioned ports. (RFC2108 rptrInfoPartitionedPorts)

rptrSegmentHealthText.name: rptrSegmentHealthText
rptrSegmentHealthText.description: Description of current health of all repeaters in the segment. (RFC2108 rptrHealthText)

rptrSegmentUtilization.name: rptrSegmentUtilization
rptrSegmentUtilization.description: The utilization rate over the last one second.

rptrModuleStatTable.name: rptrModuleStatTable
rptrModuleStatTable.description: ***** Deprecated and replaced by rptrChassisSegmentStatTable ***** Repeater status information at the Module level.

rptrModuleStatEntry.name: rptrModuleStatEntry
rptrModuleStatEntry.description: ***** Deprecated and replaced by rptrChassisSegmentStatEntry ***** A table entry, containing repeater status information about a single module.

rptrModuleIndex.name: rptrModuleIndex
rptrModuleIndex.description: ***** Deprecated and replaced by rptrChassisSegmentIndex ***** This index is the chassis number in the stack. The chassis at the top of the stack is number 1.

rptrModuleTotalFrames.name: rptrModuleTotalFrames
rptrModuleTotalFrames.description: ***** Deprecated and replaced by rptrChassisSegmentTotalFrames ***** The number of frames detected without errors. Includes unicast, broadcast, and multicast frames. Does not include frames received with frames too long, runt, FCS, or alignment errors. This is the sum of all valid received frames for all ports in this repeater module. (RFC2108 rptrMonitorGroupTotalFrames)

rptrModuleTotalOctets.name: rptrModuleTotalOctets
rptrModuleTotalOctets.description: ***** Deprecated and replaced by rptrChassisSegmentTotalOctets ***** The number of octets (bytes) contained in frames received that had no errors. This includes octets in unicast, broadcast, and multicast frames. It also includes octets after the start frame delimiter up to FCS but not including FCS octets. This is the sum of all valid received octets for all ports in this repeater module. (RFC2108 rptrMonitorGroupTotalOctets)

rptrModuleTotalErrors.name: rptrModuleTotalErrors
rptrModuleTotalErrors.description: ***** Deprecated and replaced by rptrChassisSegmentTotalErrors ***** The total number of errors detected. Total errors include FCS errors, alignment errors, frame too long, short events, late events, very long event, and rate mismatch errors. This is the sum of all errors for all ports in this repeater module. (RFC2108 rptrMonitorGroupTotalErrors)

rptrModuleFCSErrors.name: rptrModuleFCSErrors
rptrModuleFCSErrors.description: ***** Deprecated and replaced by rptrChassisSegmentFCSErrors ***** The number of frames detected that are free of partial octets and do not pass the FCS check. Usually caused by adapter underrun (when the adapter cant get enough bus bandwidth). FCS errors do not necessarily indicate that data has been lost.

rptrModuleAlignmentErrors.name: rptrModuleAlignmentErrors
rptrModuleAlignmentErrors.description: ***** Deprecated and replaced by rptrChassisSegmentAlignmentErrors ***** The number of frames detected that contain partial octets and do not pass the FCS check.

rptrModuleFrameTooLongs.name: rptrModuleFrameTooLongs
rptrModuleFrameTooLongs.description: ***** Deprecated and replaced by rptrChassisSegmentFrameTooLongs ***** The number of frames detected that exceed the maximum permitted frame size.

rptrModuleShortEvents.name: rptrModuleShortEvents
rptrModuleShortEvents.description: ***** Deprecated and replaced by rptrChassisSegmentShortEvents ***** The number of fragments detected with ActivityDuration less than ShortEventMaxTime (greater than 74 bit times and less than 82 bit times). Usually indicates a network topology problem.

rptrModuleRunts.name: rptrModuleRunts
rptrModuleRunts.description: ***** Deprecated and replaced by rptrChassisSegmentRunts ***** The number of frames detected that are less than the minimum permitted frame size of 64 octets but have a good FCS. Runts usually indicate collision fragments, a normal network event.

rptrModuleCollisions.name: rptrModuleCollisions
rptrModuleCollisions.description: ***** Deprecated and replaced by rptrChassisSegmentCollisions ***** Sum of all collisions for all ports in this repeater module.

rptrModuleLateEvents.name: rptrModuleLateEvents
rptrModuleLateEvents.description: ***** Deprecated and replaced by rptrChassisSegmentLateEvents ***** The number of collisions detected after the allowable detection period. Usually indicates a network topology problem, such as daisy-chaining class I 100Mbps hubs with UTP cable or a network diameter that is too wide.

rptrModuleVeryLongEvents.name: rptrModuleVeryLongEvents
rptrModuleVeryLongEvents.description: ***** Deprecated and replaced by rptrChassisSegmentVeryLongEvents ***** The number of times MAU jabber lockup protection (MJLP) was detected due to transmission of data that exceeded 5 msec in duration (octet count greater than maxFrameSize). Can indicate a faulty device or port.

rptrModuleDataRateMismatches.name: rptrModuleDataRateMismatches
rptrModuleDataRateMismatches.description: ***** Deprecated and replaced by rptrChassisSegmentDataRateMismatches ***** A count of the occurrences of out-of-specification bit rates. This indicates the number of times the FIFO buffer overruns or underruns due to transmission rate errors. This could indicate an incorrect FIFO setting on a network adapter or a faulty adapter.

rptrModuleAutoPartitions.name: rptrModuleAutoPartitions
rptrModuleAutoPartitions.description: ***** Deprecated and replaced by rptrChassisSegmentAutoPartitions ***** The number of times this port was automatically partitioned. This condition occurs when too many consecutive collisions are detected on the port. These collisions are due to excessive traffic on the segment, a malfunctioning port, or a malfunctioning adapter that is jabbering.

rptrPortStatTable.name: rptrPortStatTable
rptrPortStatTable.description: Repeater status information at the port level.

rptrPortStatEntry.name: rptrPortStatEntry
rptrPortStatEntry.description: A table entry, containing repeater status information about a single port.

rptrPortChassisIndex.name: rptrPortChassisIndex
rptrPortChassisIndex.description: Chassis number in stack. The chassis at the top is number 1.

rptrPortPartitionState.name: rptrPortPartitionState
rptrPortPartitionState.description: Indicates a port's current autopartitioned state. (RFC2108 rptrPortAutoPartitionState)

rptrPortReadableFrames.name: rptrPortReadableFrames
rptrPortReadableFrames.description: The number of frames detected without errors. Includes unicast, broadcast, and multicast frames. Does not include frames received with frames too long, runt, FCS, or alignment errors. (RFC2108 rptrMonitorPortReadableFrames)

rptrPortReadableOctets.name: rptrPortReadableOctets
rptrPortReadableOctets.description: The number of octets (bytes) contained in frames received that had no errors. This includes octets in unicast, broadcast, and multicast frames. It also includes octets after the start frame delimiter up to FCS but not including FCS octets. (RFC2108 rptrMonitorPortReadableOctets)

rptrPortFcsErrors.name: rptrPortFcsErrors
rptrPortFcsErrors.description: The number of frames detected that are free of partial octets and do not pass the FCS check. Usually caused by adapter underrun (when the adapter can't get enough bus bandwidth). FCS errors do not necessarily indicate that data has been lost. (RFC2108 rptrMonitorPortFCSErrors)

rptrPortAlignmentErrors.name: rptrPortAlignmentErrors
rptrPortAlignmentErrors.description: The number of frames detected that contain partial octets and do not pass the FCS check. (RFC2108 rptrMonitorPortAlignmentErrors)

rptrPortFrameTooLongs.name: rptrPortFrameTooLongs
rptrPortFrameTooLongs.description: The number of frames detected that exceed the maximum permitted frame size of 1518 octets. (RFC2108 rptrMonitorPortFrameTooLongs)

rptrPortShortEvents.name: rptrPortShortEvents
rptrPortShortEvents.description: The number of fragments detected with ActivityDuration less than ShortEventMaxTime (greater than 74 bit times and less than 82 bit times). Usually indicates a network topology problem. (RFC2108 rptrMonitorPortShortEvents)

rptrPortRunts.name: rptrPortRunts
rptrPortRunts.description: The number of frames detected that are less than the minimum permitted frame size of 64 octets but have a good FCS. Runts usually indicate collision fragments, a normal network event. (RFC2108 rptrMonitorPortRunts)

rptrPortCollisions.name: rptrPortCollisions
rptrPortCollisions.description: The number of collisions detected on a port. (RFC2108 rptrMonitorPortCollisions)

rptrPortLateEvents.name: rptrPortLateEvents
rptrPortLateEvents.description: The number of collisions detected after the allowable detection period. Usually indicates a network topology problem, such as daisy-chaining Class I 100Mbps hubs with UTP cable or a network diameter that is too wide. (RFC2108 rptrMonitorPortLateEvents)

rptrPortVeryLongEvents.name: rptrPortVeryLongEvents
rptrPortVeryLongEvents.description: The number of times MAU jabber lockup protection (MJLP) was detected due to transmission of data that exceeded 5 msec in duration (octet count greater than maxFramSize). Can indicate a faulty device or port. (RFC2108 rptrMonitorPortVeryLongEvents)

rptrPortDataRateMismatches.name: rptrPortDataRateMismatches
rptrPortDataRateMismatches.description: A count of the occurrences of out-of-specification bit rates. This indicates the number of times the FIFO buffer overruns or underruns due to transmission rate errors. This could indicate an incorrect FIFO setting on a network adapter or a faulty adapter. (RFC2108 rptrMonitorPortDataRateMismatches)

rptrPortAutoPartitions.name: rptrPortAutoPartitions
rptrPortAutoPartitions.description: The number of times this port was automatically partitioned. This condition occurs when 64 consecutive collisions are detected on the port. These collisions are due to excessive traffic on the segment, a malfunctioning port, or a malfunctioning adapter that is jabbering. (RFC2108 rptrMonitorPortAutoPartitions)

rptrPortTotalErrors.name: rptrPortTotalErrors
rptrPortTotalErrors.description: The total number of errors detected. Total errors include FCS errors, alignment errors, frame too long, short events, late events, very long event, rate mismatch, and symbol errors. (RFC2108 rptrMonitorPortTotalErrors)

rptrPortLastMACAddress.name: rptrPortLastMACAddress
rptrPortLastMACAddress.description: The source address of the last readable frame received by this port. If no frames have been received on this port, the length of the returned DisplayString is zero. (RFC2108 rptrAddrTrackNewLastSrcAddress)

rptrPortNumberofMACAddressChanges.name: rptrPortNumberofMACAddressChanges
rptrPortNumberofMACAddressChanges.description: The number of times that the value of rptrPortLastMACAddress has changed. The typical value for this port is 1, meaning the value of rptrPortLastMACAddress changed from all zeros to a MAC address. A high number of changes indicates a port connected to a switch or bridge. (RFC2108 rptrAddrTrackSourceAddrChanges)

rptrPortSymbolErrors.name: rptrPortSymbolErrors
rptrPortSymbolErrors.description: This counter is incremented by one each time a valid length packet was received at the port and there was at least one occurrence of an invalid data symbol. This can increment only once per valid carrier event. A collision presence at any port of the repeater containing port N will not cause this attribute to increment.

rptrChassisSegmentStatTable.name: rptrChassisSegmentStatTable
rptrChassisSegmentStatTable.description: Repeater status information by segment at the chassis level.

rptrChassisSegmentStatEntry.name: rptrChassisSegmentStatEntry
rptrChassisSegmentStatEntry.description: A table entry, containing repeater status information about a single chassis and segment.

rptrChassisIndex.name: rptrChassisIndex
rptrChassisIndex.description: This index is the chassis number in the stack. The chassis at the top of the stack is number 1.

rptrChassisSegmentIndex.name: rptrChassisSegmentIndex
rptrChassisSegmentIndex.description: This index is the segment number in the stack.

rptrChassisSegmentTotalFrames.name: rptrChassisSegmentTotalFrames
rptrChassisSegmentTotalFrames.description: The number of frames detected without errors. Includes unicast, broadcast, and multicast frames. Does not include frames received with frames too long, runt, FCS, or alignment errors. This is the sum of all valid received frames for all ports in this repeater module. (RFC2108 rptrMonitorGroupTotalFrames)

rptrChassisSegmentTotalOctets.name: rptrChassisSegmentTotalOctets
rptrChassisSegmentTotalOctets.description: The number of octets (bytes) contained in frames received that had no errors. This includes octets in unicast, broadcast, and multicast frames. It also includes octets after the start frame delimiter up to FCS but not including FCS octets. This is the sum of all valid received octets for all ports in this repeater module. (RFC2108 rptrMonitorGroupTotalOctets)

rptrChassisSegmentTotalErrors.name: rptrChassisSegmentTotalErrors
rptrChassisSegmentTotalErrors.description: The total number of errors detected. Total errors include FCS errors, alignment errors, frame too long, short events, late events, very long event, and rate mismatch errors. This is the sum of all errors for all ports in this repeater module. (RFC2108 rptrMonitorGroupTotalErrors)

rptrChassisSegmentFCSErrors.name: rptrChassisSegmentFCSErrors
rptrChassisSegmentFCSErrors.description: The number of frames detected that are free of partial octets and do not pass the FCS check. Usually caused by adapter underrun (when the adapter can't get enough bus bandwidth). FCS errors do not necessarily indicate that data has been lost.

rptrChassisSegmentAlignmentErrors.name: rptrChassisSegmentAlignmentErrors
rptrChassisSegmentAlignmentErrors.description: The number of frames detected that contain partial octets and do not pass the FCS check.

rptrChassisSegmentFrameTooLongs.name: rptrChassisSegmentFrameTooLongs
rptrChassisSegmentFrameTooLongs.description: The number of frames detected that exceed the maximum permitted frame size.

rptrChassisSegmentShortEvents.name: rptrChassisSegmentShortEvents
rptrChassisSegmentShortEvents.description: The number of fragments detected with ActivityDuration less than ShortEventMaxTime (greater than 74 bit times and less than 82 bit times). Usually indicates a network topology problem.

rptrChassisSegmentRunts.name: rptrChassisSegmentRunts
rptrChassisSegmentRunts.description: The number of frames detected that are less than the minimum permitted frame size of 64 octets but have a good FCS. Runts usually indicate collision fragments, a normal network event.

rptrChassisSegmentCollisions.name: rptrChassisSegmentCollisions
rptrChassisSegmentCollisions.description: Sum of all collisions for all ports in this repeater module.

rptrChassisSegmentLateEvents.name: rptrChassisSegmentLateEvents
rptrChassisSegmentLateEvents.description: The number of collisions detected after the allowable detection period. Usually indicates a network topology problem, such as daisy-chaining class I 100Mbps hubs with UTP cable or a network diameter that is too wide.

rptrChassisSegmentVeryLongEvents.name: rptrChassisSegmentVeryLongEvents
rptrChassisSegmentVeryLongEvents.description: The number of times MAU jabber lockup protection (MJLP) was detected due to transmission of data that exceeded 5 msec in duration (octet count greater than maxFrameSize). Can indicate a faulty device or port.

rptrChassisSegmentDataRateMismatches.name: rptrChassisSegmentDataRateMismatches
rptrChassisSegmentDataRateMismatches.description: A count of the occurrences of out-of-specification bit rates. This indicates the number of times the FIFO buffer overruns or underruns due to transmission rate errors. This could indicate an incorrect FIFO setting on a network adapter or a faulty adapter.

rptrChassisSegmentAutoPartitions.name: rptrChassisSegmentAutoPartitions
rptrChassisSegmentAutoPartitions.description: The number of times this port was automatically partitioned. This condition occurs when too many consecutive collisions are detected on the port. These collisions are due to excessive traffic on the segment, a malfunctioning port, or a malfunctioning adapter that is jabbering.

rptrChassisSegmentSymbolErrors.name: rptrChassisSegmentSymbolErrors
rptrChassisSegmentSymbolErrors.description: This counter is incremented by one when a valid length packet was received at the port and there was at least one occurrence of an invalid data symbol. This can increment only once per valid carrier event. A collision presence at any port of the repeater containing port N will not cause this attribute to increment.

tBrdgAdminEntry.name: tBrdgAdminEntry
tBrdgAdminEntry.description: A table entry, containing administration information for a single embedded transparent bridge span.

tBrdgAdminSpanIndex.name: tBrdgAdminSpanIndex
tBrdgAdminSpanIndex.description: Embedded transparent bridge span number. A bridge span consists of one or more embedded transparent bridges forwarding packets between two segments.

tBrdgAdminState.name: tBrdgAdminState
tBrdgAdminState.description: The state of the embedded transparent bridging span. enable - Allows packets to be forwarded by embedded bridging to the peer segment. disable - Prevents packets from being forwarded by embedded bridging to the peer segment.

tBrdgReset.name: tBrdgReset
tBrdgReset.description: 'reset' resets all enabled transparent bridges in the span. 'resetCounters' clears all transparent bridge statistics.

tBrdgThrshld.name: tBrdgThrshld
tBrdgThrshld.description: If the number of times the transparent bridge indicates buffer full exceeds this value, a trap is generated. Use 0 to disable. This trap is based on the number of tBrdgBufferFullCount in the last tBrdgPeriod.

tBrdgPeriod.name: tBrdgPeriod
tBrdgPeriod.description: Time period (in minutes) that the transparent bridge buffer full count must exceed the trap threshold value in order to generate a trap.

tBrdgLockout.name: tBrdgLockout
tBrdgLockout.description: Prevents embedded transparent bridging from being enabled or disabled via a button on the front of a hub or by the local management console interface.

tBrdgHubId.name: tBrdgHubId
tBrdgHubId.description: chassisConfigTableIndex of the chassis containing the primary internal bridge for the span. All internal bridge statistics are reported as ports 101 and 102 within this hub chassis.

tBrdgSegments.name: tBrdgSegments
tBrdgSegments.description: Embedded transparent bridge span segments. This is a list of segments (1 per byte) in this bridge span.

tBrdgStatsEntry.name: tBrdgStatsEntry
tBrdgStatsEntry.description: A table entry, containing statistics for a single embedded transparent bridge span domain.

tBrdgStatsSpan.name: tBrdgStatsSpan
tBrdgStatsSpan.description: Embedded transparent bridge span number. A bridge span consists of one or more embedded transparent bridges forwarding packets between two segments.

tBrdgStatsSegment.name: tBrdgStatsSegment
tBrdgStatsSegment.description: Embedded transparent bridge statistics segment. This index specifies which segment is associated with the transparent bridge statistics.

tBrdgUtilIn.name: tBrdgUtilIn
tBrdgUtilIn.description: The percentage of this segment's traffic that was bridged from the peer segment during the previous second.

tBrdgUtilOut.name: tBrdgUtilOut
tBrdgUtilOut.description: The percentage of this segment's traffic which was bridged to the peer segment during the previous second.

tBrdgBufferFullCount.name: tBrdgBufferFullCount
tBrdgBufferFullCount.description: The number of times internal buffer capacity was exceeded while bridging frames out of this segment.
